3806static inline bool InRange(unsigned c, unsigned lower, unsigned upper)
3807{
3808 return c >= lower && c <= upper;
3809}
3810
3811static inline unsigned gb4lin_to_gb(unsigned gb4lin)
3812{
3813 unsigned a, b, c, d;
3814 a = 0x81 + gb4lin / 12600;
3815 b = 0x30 + (gb4lin / 1260) % 10;
3816 c = 0x81 + (gb4lin / 10) % 126;
3817 d = 0x30 + gb4lin % 10;
3818 return ((a << 24) | (b << 16) | (c << 8) | d);
3819}
3820
3821static int qt_UnicodeToGb18030(unsigned uni, uint8_t *gbchar) {
3822 /* Returns the bytesize of the GB18030 character. */
3823 unsigned gb, gb4lin;
3824 indexTbl_t u2g;
3825
3826 if (uni < 0x80) {
3827 *gbchar = (uint8_t)uni;
3828 return 1;
3829 }
3830 else if (uni <= 0xD7FF || InRange(uni, 0xE766, 0xFFFF)) {
3831 u2g = ucs_to_gb18030_index[uni >> 8];
3832
3833 if ((uint8_t)(uni & 0xFF) >= u2g.tblBegin && (uint8_t)(uni & 0xFF) <= u2g.tblEnd) {
3834 // Use mapping table (2-byte or 4-byte GB18030)
3835 unsigned tblEntry;
3836
3837 tblEntry = ucs_to_gb18030[uni - u2g.tblOffset];
3838
3839 if (tblEntry > 0x8000) {
3840 // 2-byte GB18030
3841 gb = tblEntry;
3842 }
3843 else {
3844 // 4-byte GB18030 stored in a special compact format
3845 uint8_t a, b;
3846 a = 0x81;
3847 b = 0x30 + (tblEntry >> 11);
3848 if (tblEntry >= 0x7000) {
3849 a += 3;
3850 b -= 14;
3851 }
3852 else if (tblEntry >= 0x6000) {
3853 a += 2;
3854 b -= 6;
3855 }
3856 else if (tblEntry >= 0x3000) {
3857 a += 1;
3858 b -= 6;
3859 }
3860 else if (b >= 0x31) {
3861 b += 5;
3862 }
3863 gbchar[0] = a;
3864 gbchar[1] = b;
3865 gbchar[2] = 0x81 + ((tblEntry >> 4) & 0x7F);
3866 gbchar[3] = 0x30 + (tblEntry & 0xF);
3867 return 4;
3868 }
3869 }
3870 else {
3871 // 4-byte GB18030 calculated algorithmically
3872 gb4lin = u2g.algOffset + (uni & 0xFF);
3873 // Yikes, my index table could not cover all the bases...
3874 if (InRange(uni, 0x49B8, 0x49FF))
3875 gb4lin -= 11;
3876 gb = gb4lin_to_gb(gb4lin);
3877 }
3878 }
3879 else if (InRange(uni, 0xE000, 0xE765)) {
3880 // User-defined areas in GB18030 (2-byte)
3881 if (uni <= 0xE233)
3882 gb = 0xAAA1 + (((uni - 0xE000) / 94) << 8) + (uni - 0xE000) % 94;
3883 else if (uni <= 0xE4C5)
3884 gb = 0xF8A1 + (((uni - 0xE234) / 94) << 8) + (uni - 0xE234) % 94;
3885 else {
3886 gb = 0xA140 + (((uni - 0xE4C6) / 96) << 8) + (uni - 0xE4C6) % 96;
3887 // Skip the gap at 0x7F
3888 if ((gb & 0xFF) >= 0x7F)
3889 gb++;
3890 }
3891 }
3892 else if (InRange(uni, 0x10000, 0x10FFFF)) {
3893 // Qt 3.x does not support beyond BMP yet, but what the heck...
3894 // (U+10000 = GB+90308130) to (U+10FFFF = GB+E3329A35)
3895 gb = gb4lin_to_gb(0x1E248 + uni);
3896 }
3897 else {
3898 // Surrogate area and other undefined/reserved areas (discard)
3899 *gbchar = 0;
3900 return 0;
3901 }
3902
3903 if (gb <= 0xFFFF) {
3904 gbchar[0] = (uint8_t)((gb >> 8) & 0xFF);
3905 gbchar[1] = (uint8_t)(gb & 0xFF);
3906 return 2;
3907 }
3908 else {
3909 gbchar[0] = (uint8_t)((gb >> 24) & 0xFF);
3910 gbchar[1] = (uint8_t)((gb >> 16) & 0xFF);
3911 gbchar[2] = (uint8_t)((gb >> 8) & 0xFF);
3912 gbchar[3] = (uint8_t)(gb & 0xFF);
3913 return 4;
3914 }
3915}
3916
3917static int qt_UnicodeToGbk(unsigned uni, uint8_t *gbchar) {
3918 /* Returns the bytesize of the GBK character. */
3919 /* Intended for improving performance of GB2312 and GBK functions. */
3920 unsigned gb;
3921 indexTbl_t u2g;
3922
3923 if (uni < 0x80) {
3924 *gbchar = (uint8_t)uni;
3925 return 1;
3926 }
3927 else if (uni <= 0xD7FF || InRange(uni, 0xE766, 0xFFFF)) {
3928 u2g = ucs_to_gb18030_index[uni >> 8];
3929
3930 if ((uint8_t)(uni & 0xFF) >= u2g.tblBegin && (uint8_t)(uni & 0xFF) <= u2g.tblEnd) {
3931 // Use mapping table (2-byte GBK or 4-byte GB18030)
3932 unsigned tblEntry;
3933
3934 tblEntry = ucs_to_gb18030[uni - u2g.tblOffset];
3935
3936 if (tblEntry > 0x8000) {
3937 // GBK
3938 gb = tblEntry;
3939 }
3940 else {
3941 // 4-byte GB18030 stored in a special compact format (discard)
3942 *gbchar = 0;
3943 return 0;
3944 }
3945 }
3946 else {
3947 // 4-byte GB18030 calculated algorithmically (discard)
3948 *gbchar = 0;
3949 return 0;
3950 }
3951 }
3952 else if (InRange(uni, 0xE000, 0xE765)) {
3953 // User-defined areas in GB18030 (2-byte)
3954 if (uni <= 0xE233)
3955 gb = 0xAAA1 + (((uni - 0xE000) / 94) << 8) + (uni - 0xE000) % 94;
3956 else if (uni <= 0xE4C5)
3957 gb = 0xF8A1 + (((uni - 0xE234) / 94) << 8) + (uni - 0xE234) % 94;
3958 else {
3959 gb = 0xA140 + (((uni - 0xE4C6) / 96) << 8) + (uni - 0xE4C6) % 96;
3960 // Skip the gap at 0x7F
3961 if ((gb & 0xFF) >= 0x7F)
3962 gb++;
3963 }
3964 }
3965 else {
3966 // Surrogate area and other undefined/reserved areas (discard)
3967 *gbchar = 0;
3968 return 0;
3969 }
3970
3971 gbchar[0] = (uint8_t)((gb >> 8) & 0xFF);
3972 gbchar[1] = (uint8_t)(gb & 0xFF);
3973 return 2;
3974}
3975
3976void GBTextEncoder::EncodeGB18030(const std::wstring& str, std::string& bytes)
3977{
3978 static const char replacement = '?';
3979 unsigned high = 0;
3980 int invalid = 0;
3981
3982 bytes.resize(4 * str.length() + 1);
3983 int index = 0;
3984
3985 uint8_t buf[4];
3986 for (size_t i = 0; i < str.length(); ++i) {
3987 unsigned ch = str[i];
3988 int len;
3989 if (high > 0) {
3990 if (ZXing::TextUtfEncoding::IsUtf16LowSurrogate(ch)) {
3991 // valid surrogate pair
3992 ++i;
3993 unsigned u = ZXing::TextUtfEncoding::CodePointFromUtf16Surrogates(high, ch);
3994 len = qt_UnicodeToGb18030(u, buf);
3995 if (len >= 2) {
3996 for (int j = 0; j<len; j++)
3997 bytes[index++] = buf[j];
3998 }
3999 else {
4000 bytes[index++] = replacement;
4001 ++invalid;
4002 }
4003 high = 0;
4004 continue;
4005 }
4006 else {
4007 bytes[index++] = replacement;
4008 ++invalid;
4009 high = 0;
4010 }
4011 }
4012
4013 if (ch < 0x80) {
4014 // ASCII
4015 bytes[index++] = static_cast<char>(ch);
4016 }
4017 else if (ZXing::TextUtfEncoding::IsUtf16HighSurrogate(ch)) {
4018 // surrogates area. check for correct encoding
4019 // we need at least one more character, first the high surrogate, then the low one
4020 high = ch;
4021 }
4022 else if ((len = qt_UnicodeToGb18030(ch, buf)) >= 2) {
4023 for (int j = 0; j<len; j++)
4024 bytes[index++] = buf[j];
4025 }
4026 else {
4027 // Error
4028 bytes[index++] = replacement;
4029 ++invalid;
4030 }
4031 }
4032 bytes.resize(index);
4033}
4034
4035void GBTextEncoder::EncodeGB2312(const std::wstring& str, std::string& bytes)
4036{
4037 static const char replacement = '?';
4038 //int invalid = 0;
4039
4040 bytes.resize(2 * str.length() + 1);
4041 int index = 0;
4042
4043 uint8_t buf[2];
4044 for (wchar_t ch : str) {
4045 if (ch < 0x80) {
4046 // ASCII
4047 bytes[index++] = static_cast<char>(ch);
4048 }
4049 else if ((qt_UnicodeToGbk(ch, buf) == 2) &&
4050 (buf[0] >= 0xA1) && (buf[1] >= 0xA1)) {
4051 bytes[index++] = buf[0];
4052 bytes[index++] = buf[1];
4053 }
4054 else {
4055 // Error
4056 bytes[index++] = replacement;
4057 //++invalid;
4058 }
4059 }
4060 bytes.resize(index);
4061}
